      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <updateDate>2015-04-16T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Steve Gleason Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to cover as durable medical equipment any eye tracking and gaze interaction accessories for speech generating devices furnished to individuals with a demonstrated medical need for them.</p> <p>Payment for speech generating devices or accessories furnished during FY2015-FY2018 shall be made on a rental basis, or in a lump-sum amount for the purchase of the item, without a cap on the amount.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-04-28T15:05:51Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2015-04-16</actionDate>
        </item>
        <item>
          <updateDate>2015-04-22T12:42:17Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</p> <p><b>Steve Gleason Act of 2015</b></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to cover as durable medical equipment any eye tracking and gaze interaction accessories for speech generating devices furnished to individuals with a demonstrated medical need for them.</p> <p>(Sec. 3) Payment for speech generating devices or accessories shall be made on a rental basis, or in a lump-sum amount for the purchase of the item, without a cap on the amount in the case of devices furnished on or after October 1, 2015, and before October 1, 2018.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Passed Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-04-23T21:05:31Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Passed Senate without amendment</name>
          <versionCode>82</versionCode>
